Package: craft
Type: Package
Title: A CRAFT Pipeline for Evaluating LLM-Generated Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Yuehong Cassandra", "Tai",
           email = "yuehongtai@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(affiliation = "Pennsylvania State University")),
    person("Hyein", "Ko",
           email = "hyein.ko@cwru.edu",
           role = "aut",
           comment = c(affiliation = "Case Western Reserve University")))
Description: Implements the CRAFT framework (Construct, Report, Assess,
    Field-audit, Translate) for evaluating data generated by large
    language models in political and social science research. Provides
    a unified interface to multiple inter-rater reliability metrics
    (Cohen's kappa, weighted kappa, Fleiss' kappa, Krippendorff's
    alpha, ICC, percent agreement), validity metrics (precision,
    recall, F1, MCC, balanced accuracy), cross-prompt and cross-model
    stability comparison, rationale audit helpers, and a design-based
    supervised learning (DSL) wrapper for propagating annotation
    uncertainty into downstream inference. The 'report()'
    function emits a reproducibility report that captures the LLM
    version, prompt text, metric values, thresholds, and audit
    decisions used in a study.
